  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        patients with shock
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age â‰¥ 18 years admitted to the participating hospital.

          -  Patients in the emergency department, intensive care unit, PACU, or any hospital
             floor. For patients not in the ICU, there must be plans to transfer to an intensive
             care unit when an ICU bed is available for patient.

          -  Patients with shock as defined by:

          -  Need for vasopressor (dopamine, norepinephrine, or epinephrine at any dose) to keep
             MAP &gt; 65 mmHg Or

          -  Systolic BP &lt; 90 mmHg

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients previously enrolled into this study.

          -  Patients who were in the operating room at time of shock and fluid bolus.

          -  Patients admitted to an ICU after cardiac surgery Patients with primarily cardiogenic
             shock as etiology for their shock

          -  Patients transferred from another hospital or emergency room to the study hospital.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
